text: Macauley King (born 4 October 1995) is an English footballer who plays as a defender for El Paso Locomotive in the USL Championship. While in college, he played in the Premier Development League with Mississippi Brilla, Charlotte Eagles, and Seattle Sounders FC U-23. ==References== ==External links== *Profile at YHC Athletics Category:1995 births Category:Living people Category:English footballers Category:Mississippi Brilla players Category:Charlotte Eagles players Category:Seattle Sounders FC U-23 players Category:Indy Eleven players Category:El Paso Locomotive FC players Category:USL League Two players Category:USL Championship players Category:Association football defenders Category:English expatriate footballers Category:Expatriate soccer players in the United States Category:English expatriate sportspeople in the United States
